questionsAndAnswers.question:
Hi there,
What kind of cost is it for a normal 3 bed house and are there any grants / subsidies available c/o the council??

Regards,
Neville

answers.answer:
Hi Neville, 

There are two incentives available. These are Feed in tariff for Solar panel installations and Renewable heat incentive for Air source/ground source heat pumps. Unfortunately there are no grants available from local council.

If you would like a quote for either technologies please call our offices and arrange for a site visit 01522 700281.

Thank you for your question,
UK Eco Energy Solutions Team

reviews.name: Jane Bartle
reviews.text: From start to finish attention to detail was excellent.  All aspects of the work from inception, planning and delivery were brilliant.  Staff were attentive, accommodating, pleasant and extremely professional.  We would certainly recommend them.

reviews.name: Lorraine Harvey
reviews.text: We recently had solar panels & battery installed.From start to finish the service was second to none.David Nash MD came by appointment to explain the process & answer our many questions without any pressure on us to proceed. This was the first company we approached as we wished to go locally and was left in no doubt this was the company for us. The whole team, led personally by David, of scaffolder’s, fitters, electricians and admin team gave excellent service. You are definitely a client, not a number. Huge thank you to the whole team.

reviews.name: Cliff Moss
reviews.text:
I had UK ECO ENERGY fit solar panels . The project from start to finish was seamless. Kirk who came to advise us was informative and did give us excellent advice.
The survey was done throughly and the team that came to fit the panels in cold damp weather made an excellent job and cleaned up immaculately even replaced a damaged tile they spotted on a different part of the roof .
The electricians who came to fit and connect everything just as perfectly. Everything explained well .
Tip keep both teams well watered with tea.
I have now had these panels for 3 months and the are more efficient that I expected even in the overcast days .
In the recent sunny weather I’m using no electricity from the grid and supplying EON a significant amount each day .
Also a big thank you to the office staff for help .
I would highly recommend this company .
